1157
Your Honor,

I appear before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I fully acknowledge my actions and accept the responsibility for the resulting consequences.

On the day in question, I deeply regret that my sense of urgency to pick up my family members at the airport clouded my judgment. I engaged in aggressive driving, exceeding the speed limit, and foolishly answered a text message while operating the vehicle. Unfortunately, this led to a collision with a guardrail. I am grateful that no one else was harmed in the accident.

I acknowledge that I already have 3 penalty points on my license for a previous speeding offense. This serves as a reminder of the importance of abiding by traffic laws. This incident has truly been an awakening for me; I now fully understand the dangers associated with my reckless actions.

In reflecting upon this incident, I have come to realize the serious potential harm I could have caused not only to myself but also to others. I am truly remorseful for jeopardizing the safety of those around me and the anxiety my actions may have caused them.

While pleading guilty is in itself an admission of fault, I would like to bring to the court's attention some information regarding my character. I am 37 years old and have maintained an exemplary record up until this point. This incident stands as an isolated mistake in an otherwise law-abiding life. Additionally, I have been a consistent supporter of the British Heart Foundation, demonstrating my commitment to making a positive impact on society.

In light of these factors, I humbly request the court's leniency in considering my case. Although I fully comprehend the recklessness of my actions, I assure the court that this event has made a lasting impact on my perspective, and I am resolute in taking the necessary measures to prevent any recurrence of such behavior.

Thank you, Your Honor, for your kind consideration. I willingly accept the consequences of my actions and will make every effort to rectify the harm I have caused.

