I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I fully acknowledge my complete responsibility for my actions and the potential harm they could have caused.

On the day in question, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. Regrettably, I allowed my sense of urgency to cloud my judgment, leading me to drive aggressively and exceed the speed limit. Additionally, I made the poor decision to answer a text message while driving, further diverting my attention from the road. As a result, I collided with a guardrail. Fortunately, no one else was hurt in this incident.

Having taken time to reflect upon this incident, I now fully comprehend the severity of the danger my actions posed not only to myself but also to all those sharing the road with me. I deeply regret the potential harm I could have caused and the fear my reckless behavior may have instilled in others.

Furthermore, I would like to highlight that my guilty plea is a sincere acknowledgment of the seriousness of my actions and serves as a mitigating factor. I understand the need for accountability, and I am prepared to accept the consequences for my careless driving.

Thank you, Your Honor, for your understanding and consideration of my case. I trust that my guilty plea and genuine remorse will be seen as positive contributions to the court's assessment of my case and the appropriate sentence.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter

